directory: template/.github/workflows
domain: Defines the GitHub Actions CI entry point for the templated Rust project: triggers on push to main and on pull requests, provisions the toolchain and lint/audit tools, then hands off to scripts/ci.sh for the actual checks. This directory's contract with the rest of the repo is thin — it must stay in sync with scripts/ci.sh's tool requirements and with rust-toolchain.toml.
edit_notes:
  - Adding/removing a required CI tool means updating both ci.yml's install steps and scripts/ci.sh; neither alone is sufficient.
  - Rust toolchain version is sourced from rust-toolchain.toml, not hardcoded here.
children:
  - ci.yml: single-job CI workflow (toolchain + tool setup, delegates checks to scripts/ci.sh)
invariants:
  - All checks run sequentially in one ubuntu-latest job; no matrix builds.
  - Installed CI tools (cargo-deny, cargo-machete, cargo-modules) resolve versions via `--locked` against their own lockfiles, independent of repo Cargo.lock.